          "prompt_html": "<h1>MULTIPLE CHOICE 45</h1><p><strong>Questions 37 - 40</strong></p><p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A, B or C</strong>.</p><p>37 When did volcanic activity begin in the Yellowstone National Park region?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    2 million years ago</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    1.5 million years ago</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    640,000 years ago</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>38 What have scientists stated regarding the history of eruptions at Yellowstone Park?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    The eruptions always get bigger.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    The eruptions have a recognisable pattern over time.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    Magma levels have never been an indication to when eruptions happen.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>39 What job will the proposed task force have regarding a possible future super eruption in Yellowstone Park?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    Predicting the eruption</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    Crisis management</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    Measuring lava levels</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>40 What evidence has been used by scientists to claim that the Toba eruption caused catastrophic climate change?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    Genetic material found</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    Archaeological rock layers</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    Cave paintings discovered in Sumatra</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table>",
